[src:less-css/css-cascade-specificity] The last selector has four *TYPE* components.
[src:less-css/css-cascade-specificity] While it has the highest integer value, no matter how many elements and pseudo-elements are included, even if there were 150, TYPE components never have precedence over *CLASS* components.
[src:less-css/css-cascade-specificity] The column values are compared starting from left to right when column values are equal.
[src:less-css/css-cascade-specificity] When multiple declarations have equal specificity, the last declaration found in the CSS is applied to the element.
