[src:less-css/css-css-nesting] The **CSS nesting** module defines a syntax for nesting selectors, providing the ability to nest one style rule inside another, with the selector of the child rule relative to the selector of the parent rule.
[src:less-css/css-css-nesting] CSS nesting is different from CSS preprocessors such as Sass in that it is parsed by the browser rather than being pre-compiled by a CSS preprocessor.
[src:less-css/css-css-nesting] CSS nesting helps with the readability, modularity, and maintainability of CSS stylesheets.
[src:less-css/css-css-nesting] It also potentially helps reduce the size of CSS files, thereby decreasing the amount of data downloaded by users.
