[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Mixins allows embedding all the properties of a class into another class by including the class name as one of its property, thus behaving as a sort of constant or variable.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] They can also behave like functions, and take arguments.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] CSS does not support Mixins: Any repeated code must be repeated in each location.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Mixins allows for more efficient and clean code repetitions, as well as easier alteration of code.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Less has a special type of ruleset called parametric mixins which can be mixed in like classes, but accepts parameters.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Operations allow addition, subtraction, division and multiplication of property values and colors, which can be used to create complex relationships between properties.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Functions map one-to-one with JavaScript code, allowing manipulation of values.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Both Sass and Less are CSS preprocessors, which allow writing clean CSS in a programming construct instead of static rules.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Sass was designed to both simplify and extend CSS, so things like curly braces were removed from the syntax.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Less was designed to be as close to CSS as possible, and as a result existing CSS can be used as valid Less code.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] The newer versions of Sass also introduced a CSS-like syntax called SCSS (Sassy CSS).
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Less can be applied to sites in a number of ways.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] One option is to include the less.js JavaScript file to convert the code on-the-fly.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] The browser then renders the output CSS.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] Another option is to render the Less code into pure CSS and upload the CSS to a site.
[src:less-css/less-style-sheet-language] With this option no .less files are uploaded and the site does not need the less.js JavaScript converter.
